The paper deals with the problem of multitask learning, which is a common topic in machine learning. The focus of the paper is on learning multiple tasks that are related by a system of nonlinear equations, which suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of structured prediction, which is a technique commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV), suggesting that the paper could also be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of regularization approaches, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) and neural networks (NE), suggesting that the paper could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
